article.description: — Caleb Asberry had 20 points as Texas State topped Incarnate Word 75-57 in a season opener on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Asberry leads Texas State past Incarnate Word 75-57
article.linkText: Asberry leads Texas State past Incarnate Word 75-57
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Caleb Asberry had 20 points as Texas State topped Incarnate Word 75-57 in a season opener on Tuesday night. Shelby Adams had 14 points for Texas State. Drue Drinnon added 12 points. Josh Morgan had 16 points for the Cardinals. Johnny Hughes III added 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
